<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="276" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Cridler</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Goodnow</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-08"><hi rend="italic">August 8,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Minister Wu officially communicated to-day Imperial edict 5th
                                instant, allowing free cipher communication between ministers and
                                Governments.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cridler.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>